<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="324" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10793/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Heimke</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-07"><hi rend="italic">January 7,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Advise Government of Guatemala that Maj. Gen. George W. Davis, former
                            military governor of Porto Rico, former commanding general of the
                            Philippines, and former President of Panama Canal Commission, leaves
                            to-day with his secretary accredited as minister on special mission to
                            represent the United States at opening of railroad.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>